
#LeetCode problem link- https://leetcode.com/problems/missing-number/
#Amazon 

Statement- Given an array nums containing n distinct numbers in the range [0, n], return the only number in the range that is missing from the array.

Solution- public int missingNumber(int[] nums) {
            int i=0;
            while(i<nums.length) {
                int correct=nums[i]; //finding the correct index
                if(nums[i]<nums.length && nums[i]!=nums[correct]) { 
                    int temp=nums[i];
                    nums[i]=nums[correct];
                    nums[correct]=temp;
                }
                else { //increment the i value if element is at correct index
                    i++;
                }
            }	
            for(int index=0;index<nums.length;index++){
                if(nums[index]!=index){
                    return index;
                }
            }
            return nums.length;
        }
